# Backend SOLID And Module Structure

- Keep modules and functions small and single-purpose (target: ~200 lines per file, ~40 lines per function where practical).
- Prefer adding focused modules in one package folder (for example `backend/bookings/domain/`) instead of expanding large files.
- Split responsibilities by layer:
  - views/controllers: request/response orchestration only
  - services/domain: business logic and policies
  - models: persistence and minimal domain behavior
- Avoid duplicate logic; extract shared helpers/constants and reuse from one source of truth.
- Keep dependencies directional: controllers may depend on services; services/domain should not depend on framework response objects.
- Preserve behavior for safe refactors (no API shape or status code changes unless explicitly requested).

## Example

```python
# BAD: view handles business policy inline
if booking.status == BookingStatus.CANCELLED:
    return Response({ERROR_KEY: BOOKING_CANCELLED_MSG})

# GOOD: view delegates policy to domain helper
is_valid, error_payload = validate_ticket_state(ticket)
if not is_valid:
    return Response(error_payload)
```
